content: A whole new way to cook. Sous vide! (pronounced soo veed). My awesome partner Lori got me the white cylander you see here for my b'day. It is a JOULE SOUS VIDE cooker. Basically, the way it works, you put meat or vegetables in a baggie, seal it, put it in water in a pot off the stove, immerse the sous vide machine, set it to the proper temperature, it cooks and you don't have to worry about anything over overcooking. After the protein comes to temperature, you take it out and see it on each side for about a minute. I promise you, the best steak, chicken, fish or vegetables you've ever had. #abc7NY
